The result of the voting was then declared by the president, and the sentence, whether fine, loss of political rights, or banishment, im- mediately carried into effect.

The judges (iudices), or jury, as we should rather

² call them, were originally chosen from the senators

by mutual agreement. Gaius Gracchus introduced a list (affiwm, so called from the names being written in black letters on a board chalked or painted white) of iudices for the quaestiones perpetuae. This list, at first a permanent one, was afterwards annually re- vised by the praetor urbanus: during the Empire, the jury were nominated by the Emper0r0for life.
